# C++, Console App (VisualStudio IDE / Windows Host)

### Software/Tools Needed
* Visual Studio

## Set Up

1. Create New C++ Empty Project
2. Add new CPP file to source files (best practice, name it main.cpp)

## Hello World

1. Add standard input/output library

       #include <iostream>
       
2. Add main function

       void main()
       {
           return;
       }

3. Add simple output in your main function

       std::cout << "Hello World!";

4. Build and Run

##### Full Code

    #inculude <iostream>
    void main()
    {
        std::cout << "Hello World";
        return;
    }

